{"article_id":"oPSjwo1MLkLd3zaP","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The nature of the events","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"that led ex-FBI Director James Comey to testify before the Senate Select Committee on Intelligence Thursday","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"are extraordinary .","depth":5},{"id":3,"text":"Comey ' s testimony of his version of events was even more so .","depth":4},{"id":4,"text":"Starting with Comey ' s sudden firing on May 9 ,","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"events have been unfolding since then , with near-daily scoops about the interactions between Trump and Comey and the campaigns connections to Russia","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"- it has been a wild ride up until this point .","depth":5},{"id":7,"text":"Most of what we knew before Thursday has come in bits and pieces .","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"Journalists outside the White House","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"( and the public )","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"have struggled to put together scraps from anonymous sources ,","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"often only revealing a little information at a time .","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"Comey ' s prepared testimony ,","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"released Wednesday afternoon ,","depth":10},{"id":14,"text":"gave the public a narrative :","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"that President Donald Trump consistently either failed to understand or intentionally violated the norms of independence","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"that set the FBI out of political reach .","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"Comey ' s testimony Thursday presented a reliable narrator for that story .","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"And the dogged questioning from Democrats","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"- and , often , Republicans -","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"made for high drama","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"that drew its power not from partisan confrontation , but from the excitement","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"of finding out the truth .","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"The political fight over Comey ' s firing , and the broader Russia scandal , is ongoing .","depth":5},{"id":24,"text":"Here ' s who came out of Thursday ' s hearing in a stronger position","depth":6},{"id":25,"text":"- and who saw themselves undermined .","depth":6},{"id":26,"text":"The clip","depth":12},{"id":27,"text":"that sums up Thursday ' s hearing","depth":12},{"id":28,"text":"isn ' t actually from the hearing at all .","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"It ' s from the moments before the hearing ,","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"as a low-grade hurricane of Senate business swirled around an implacable Comey at its eye .","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"That image","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"- an unruffled professional ,","depth":12},{"id":33,"text":"speaking on behalf of no one but himself","depth":13},{"id":34,"text":"and prompted by nothing but his own sense of right and wrong -","depth":13},{"id":35,"text":"is the one","depth":11},{"id":36,"text":"Comey projected throughout the hearing .","depth":11},{"id":37,"text":"It was a masterful performance .","depth":8},{"id":38,"text":"Comey presented himself as a career government man","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"who knew enough","depth":11},{"id":40,"text":"not to trust a strange new president","depth":12},{"id":41,"text":"already surrounded by scandal ,","depth":12},{"id":42,"text":"but who nonetheless deferred to him , as president , up to the point","depth":12},{"id":43,"text":"where doing so would violate the law","depth":12},{"id":44,"text":"-","depth":11},{"id":45,"text":"and whose primary concern , even then , was to protect the investigation","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"rather than to cause trouble","depth":11},{"id":47,"text":"he saw as unnecessary with the president .","depth":11},{"id":48,"text":"In doing so ,","depth":7},{"id":49,"text":"he made himself extremely hard to impugn .","depth":8},{"id":50,"text":"Even his toughest Republican questioners were forced to acknowledge his basic integrity , and take the gravity of his claims at least somewhat seriously .","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"( One of the president ' s most vociferous defenders , Sen. John Cornyn , ended up arguing","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"that the president wasn ' t guilty of obstructing justice","depth":11},{"id":53,"text":"because Comey disobeyed his request","depth":12},{"id":54,"text":"to drop the investigation into former National Security Adviser Mike Flynn . )","depth":12},{"id":55,"text":"He won ' t remain above the fray forever .","depth":6},{"id":56,"text":"Some of his answers","depth":12},{"id":57,"text":"about why he didn ' t do more , at the time ,","depth":13},{"id":58,"text":"to raise alarms about the president ' s behavior","depth":13},{"id":59,"text":"aren ' t likely to satisfy Republicans ,","depth":11},{"id":60,"text":"and it ' s likely they ' ll paint him as a disgruntled ex-employee","depth":12},{"id":61,"text":"smearing his former boss","depth":12},{"id":62,"text":"( or as a \" deep-state \" mole","depth":12},{"id":63,"text":"opposed to Trump from the beginning ) .","depth":12},{"id":64,"text":"But","depth":10},{"id":65,"text":"while his admission","depth":13},{"id":66,"text":"that \" I could have been stronger \"","depth":14},{"id":67,"text":"in pushing back against Trump in the moment","depth":14},{"id":68,"text":"might be a political liability for him ,","depth":12},{"id":69,"text":"it rang true .","depth":11},{"id":70,"text":"It confirmed ,","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"as much","depth":11},{"id":72,"text":"as anyone has ever confirmed on the record , something","depth":12},{"id":73,"text":"that many people assume","depth":14},{"id":74,"text":"is true","depth":14},{"id":75,"text":"but few can prove :","depth":13},{"id":76,"text":"that this president is fundamentally not normal ,","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"that he fundamentally will not play by the rules","depth":11},{"id":78,"text":"that protect the integrity of his office and the government .","depth":11},{"id":79,"text":"Faced with such a boss ,","depth":12},{"id":80,"text":"we all think","depth":13},{"id":81,"text":"we ' d be the first","depth":14},{"id":82,"text":"to blow the whistle .","depth":14},{"id":83,"text":"But many of us wouldn ' t .","depth":11},{"id":84,"text":"Jim Comey simply admitted to it .","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"Remember in the days before the election ,","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"when liberals were all worried","depth":11},{"id":87,"text":"that the FBI ' s support for Trump had corrupted the agency ' s law enforcement capabilities ?","depth":11},{"id":88,"text":"The FBI was never the most likely agency","depth":11},{"id":89,"text":"for critics of Trump to look to as the \" resistance \" within the federal government .","depth":11},{"id":90,"text":"But the president ' s unseemly interest in the Russia investigation appears to have set them on edge","depth":11},{"id":91,"text":"- and firing their director only made the problem worse .","depth":11},{"id":92,"text":"Comey made an impassioned case for the independence and professionalism of his former agency before the committee .","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"\" There is no one indispensable person , \"","depth":12},{"id":94,"text":"he said in the hearing ' s biggest humblebrag ;","depth":12},{"id":95,"text":"the work","depth":13},{"id":96,"text":"of investigating the Trump campaign","depth":13},{"id":97,"text":"will continue .","depth":12},{"id":98,"text":"The idea of the FBI as a bastion of integrity within the federal government isn ' t just amusing","depth":6},{"id":99,"text":"because of the agency ' s history","depth":7},{"id":100,"text":"( the shadow of J. Edgar Hoover still looms large , to the point","depth":8},{"id":101,"text":"where the founding director was mentioned in passing on Thursday as an example of inappropriate power over a president ) .","depth":8},{"id":102,"text":"It ' s fascinating","depth":7},{"id":103,"text":"because , as recently as last fall , it really looked like the political persuasion of the agency ' s field officers were going to undermine its commitment to investigating wrongdoing .","depth":7},{"id":104,"text":"Instead , though , it appears that many FBI agents","depth":9},{"id":105,"text":"who had supported Trump","depth":9},{"id":106,"text":"are putting their agency over their party .","depth":8},{"id":107,"text":"They may not be as noble","depth":9},{"id":108,"text":"as Comey made them look Thursday ,","depth":9},{"id":109,"text":"but they ' re certainly looking better","depth":9},{"id":110,"text":"than one might have expected .","depth":9},{"id":111,"text":"You might be surprised to hear this ,","depth":6},{"id":112,"text":"but senators like to hear themselves talk .","depth":7},{"id":113,"text":"They like to hear themselves talk on television and in the halls of Congress .","depth":7},{"id":114,"text":"If the members of the intelligence committee had used the opportunity of a televised committee hearing","depth":9},{"id":115,"text":"to grandstand about how terrible Trump was","depth":12},{"id":116,"text":"( or how terrible the media was )","depth":12},{"id":117,"text":"for seven minutes at a time ,","depth":11},{"id":118,"text":"barely letting Comey get a word in edgewise ,","depth":10},{"id":119,"text":"it would have made for deadly viewing .","depth":8},{"id":120,"text":"That wasn ' t what happened .","depth":8},{"id":121,"text":"Members of both parties managed to restrain themselves from pontificating about what they thought","depth":11},{"id":122,"text":"the problem was","depth":11},{"id":123,"text":"( with the exception of a little bit of Russia-bashing from ranking member Sen. Mark Warner","depth":11},{"id":124,"text":"( D-VA ) ) .","depth":11},{"id":125,"text":"And members of both parties , but particularly Democrats , made a point of sticking to questions","depth":10},{"id":126,"text":"either that Comey could answer ,","depth":11},{"id":127,"text":"or that his refusal or inability","depth":13},{"id":128,"text":"to discuss","depth":13},{"id":129,"text":"would be an answer of a different kind .","depth":12},{"id":130,"text":"Sen. Ron Wyden","depth":9},{"id":131,"text":"( D-OR )","depth":9},{"id":132,"text":"is a veteran of this kind of questioning .","depth":8},{"id":133,"text":"As one of the Senate ' s leading critics of government surveillance , he ' s well-trained in the art","depth":11},{"id":134,"text":"of asking a witness a question","depth":12},{"id":135,"text":"he knows","depth":13},{"id":136,"text":"the witness can ' t answer publicly ,","depth":13},{"id":137,"text":"as a way","depth":11},{"id":138,"text":"of flagging for the public","depth":12},{"id":139,"text":"that there is something of interest","depth":13},{"id":140,"text":"being kept from them .","depth":13},{"id":141,"text":"On Thursday , he used those skills","depth":10},{"id":142,"text":"to extract one of the few genuinely new pieces of information from the hearing :","depth":11},{"id":143,"text":"that Comey had a reason ,","depth":13},{"id":144,"text":"beyond what ' s publicly been reported ,","depth":13},{"id":145,"text":"to believe","depth":13},{"id":146,"text":"that Jeff Sessions would need to recuse himself from the Russia investigation .","depth":13},{"id":147,"text":"Wyden wasn ' t flashy .","depth":9},{"id":148,"text":"He wasn ' t outraged .","depth":10},{"id":149,"text":"He simply moved the ball forward in the investigation","depth":12},{"id":150,"text":"and let Comey be the star of the show .","depth":12},{"id":151,"text":"And his colleagues followed suit .","depth":11},{"id":152,"text":"Democrats in Congress have been in a tricky position under Trump","depth":5},{"id":153,"text":"- and not just because they ' re the minority party .","depth":5},{"id":154,"text":"They ' re torn between a need","depth":6},{"id":155,"text":"to uphold the government","depth":7},{"id":156,"text":"( by helping Republicans keep it funded ,","depth":8},{"id":157,"text":"and adhering to its norms )","depth":8},{"id":158,"text":"and a desire","depth":6},{"id":159,"text":"to please a base","depth":7},{"id":160,"text":"who sees this president as fundamentally illegitimate or downright monstrous .","depth":7},{"id":161,"text":"Thursday ' s hearing showed","depth":6},{"id":162,"text":"that Democrats don ' t need to stamp their feet","depth":9},{"id":163,"text":"and gnash their teeth","depth":10},{"id":164,"text":"and wear pussy hats on the floor of the Senate","depth":10},{"id":165,"text":"to demonstrate effective opposition .","depth":8},{"id":166,"text":"They can simply show a commitment","depth":9},{"id":167,"text":"to finding the truth ,","depth":9},{"id":168,"text":"and a confidence","depth":9},{"id":169,"text":"that the truth will","depth":12},{"id":170,"text":"not","depth":13},{"id":171,"text":"-","depth":13},{"id":172,"text":"as the truth so far has not -","depth":11},{"id":173,"text":"make the Trump administration look very good .","depth":10},{"id":174,"text":"Here are things","depth":8},{"id":175,"text":"said about the president of the United States by the former FBI director :","depth":8},{"id":176,"text":"\" The nature of the person -","depth":9},{"id":177,"text":"I was honestly concerned","depth":11},{"id":178,"text":"he might lie about the nature of our meeting","depth":11},{"id":179,"text":"so I thought it important to document . \"","depth":10},{"id":180,"text":"\" The administration then chose to defame me and , more importantly , the FBI","depth":10},{"id":181,"text":"by saying","depth":12},{"id":182,"text":"that the organization was in disarray ,","depth":13},{"id":183,"text":"that it was poorly led ,","depth":14},{"id":184,"text":"that the workforce had lost confidence in its leader .","depth":14},{"id":185,"text":"Those were lies , plain and simple . \"","depth":11},{"id":186,"text":"\" I was so stunned by the conversation","depth":10},{"id":187,"text":"that I just took it in . \"","depth":10},{"id":188,"text":"There ' s more where this came from .","depth":6},{"id":189,"text":"Nothing","depth":7},{"id":190,"text":"James Comey said about Donald Trump Thursday","depth":7},{"id":191,"text":"inspired any confidence in the leadership of the president .","depth":6},{"id":192,"text":"The only ambiguity ,","depth":9},{"id":193,"text":"which Republicans are trying to seize on , to questionable benefit ,","depth":9},{"id":194,"text":"is if the president was actively trying to undermine the rule of law","depth":9},{"id":195,"text":"by running the federal government like a family business ,","depth":9},{"id":196,"text":"or if the man with his finger on the nuclear button is so astoundingly ignorant and badly advised","depth":8},{"id":197,"text":"that he just has no idea","depth":9},{"id":198,"text":"how anything works","depth":11},{"id":199,"text":"and needs remedial lessons","depth":12},{"id":200,"text":"- that his own White House hasn ' t given him -","depth":12},{"id":201,"text":"in things like the fundamental independence of the FBI .","depth":10},{"id":202,"text":"Both of those are terrifying possibilities .","depth":7},{"id":203,"text":"Both are bad for democracy and bad for the rule of law .","depth":7},{"id":204,"text":"The best thing","depth":8},{"id":205,"text":"you can say about the president ,","depth":8},{"id":206,"text":"coming out of today ' s hearing ,","depth":7},{"id":207,"text":"is that he didn ' t make it worse for himself with aggrieved live-tweeting .","depth":6},{"id":208,"text":"But he can ' t sustain silence forever -","depth":6},{"id":209,"text":"and","depth":7},{"id":210,"text":"if everything Trump ' s done up to this point is any indication ,","depth":8},{"id":211,"text":"he ' s going to have a tough time","depth":10},{"id":212,"text":"sticking to his agenda","depth":10},{"id":213,"text":"when there ' s an insult out there","depth":10},{"id":214,"text":"he wants to rebut .","depth":10},{"id":215,"text":"The question isn ' t whether Donald Trump will respond to James Comey in a way","depth":7},{"id":216,"text":"that makes Trump look bad .","depth":7},{"id":217,"text":"It ' s when .","depth":6},{"id":218,"text":"The most tantalizing hint","depth":10},{"id":219,"text":"Comey dropped Thursday","depth":10},{"id":220,"text":"wasn ' t about Trump .","depth":9},{"id":221,"text":"It was about Attorney General Jeff Sessions .","depth":8},{"id":222,"text":"Comey said","depth":10},{"id":223,"text":"that he expected Sessions to recuse himself from the Russia investigation","depth":11},{"id":224,"text":"even before Sessions officially did so .","depth":11},{"id":225,"text":"Under questioning from Wyden , he admitted","depth":10},{"id":226,"text":"that he hadn ' t just made that assumption","depth":13},{"id":227,"text":"based on what was publicly known about the Russian Ambassador Sergey Kislyak meeting ,","depth":13},{"id":228,"text":"but based on something else","depth":14},{"id":229,"text":"he ' d known","depth":14},{"id":230,"text":"- but he wouldn ' t publicly say","depth":15},{"id":231,"text":"what that thing was","depth":15},{"id":232,"text":"( emphasis added ) :","depth":14},{"id":233,"text":"Our judgment ,","depth":14},{"id":234,"text":"as I recall ,","depth":14},{"id":235,"text":"is that he was very close to and inevitably going to recuse himself for a variety of reasons .","depth":13},{"id":236,"text":"We also were aware of facts","depth":15},{"id":237,"text":"that I ca n't discuss in an open setting","depth":15},{"id":238,"text":"that would make his continued engagement in a Russia-related investigation problematic .","depth":14},{"id":239,"text":"So we were convinced","depth":14},{"id":240,"text":"- in fact ,","depth":16},{"id":241,"text":"I think","depth":17},{"id":242,"text":"we 'd already heard","depth":17},{"id":243,"text":"that the career people were recommending","depth":16},{"id":244,"text":"that he recuse himself ,","depth":17},{"id":245,"text":"that he was not going to be in contact with Russia-related matters much longer .","depth":17},{"id":246,"text":"It ' s not clear what Comey is referring to .","depth":9},{"id":247,"text":"It ' s possible that he ' s referring to a second meeting between Sessions and Kislyak during the campaign ,","depth":13},{"id":248,"text":"reported by CNN at the end of May","depth":14},{"id":249,"text":"but not yet officially confirmed .","depth":14},{"id":250,"text":"( Having two meetings , and failing to admit to either of them during your confirmation , is a bigger sign of deliberate intent","depth":14},{"id":251,"text":"to mislead","depth":14},{"id":252,"text":"than just leaving one off . )","depth":13},{"id":253,"text":"It ' s also possible that Sessions had some other contact with Russia","depth":12},{"id":254,"text":"that hasn ' t yet been reported .","depth":12},{"id":255,"text":"Or maybe Comey was referring to something else entirely .","depth":10},{"id":256,"text":"Sessions has been the most unexpected member of the Trump administration","depth":10},{"id":257,"text":"to get caught up in the Russia scandal","depth":10},{"id":258,"text":"- unlike Trump or many of the president ' s other advisers , he ' s a career politician .","depth":9},{"id":259,"text":"He ' s already on the outs with the president for things","depth":10},{"id":260,"text":"that aren ' t related to Russia","depth":10},{"id":261,"text":"( although the president is always on the outs with someone in his White House ) .","depth":9},{"id":262,"text":"But more public scrutiny is probably the last thing","depth":9},{"id":263,"text":"he needs ,","depth":9},{"id":264,"text":"especially regarding the Comey firing saga ,","depth":9},{"id":265,"text":"which Thursday ' s testimony ensures","depth":10},{"id":266,"text":"isn ' t going away anytime soon .","depth":10},{"id":267,"text":"Let ' s start with this tweet ,","depth":6},{"id":268,"text":"sent Wednesday by the official Twitter account of the Republican National Committee","depth":7},{"id":269,"text":"after the written copy of Comey ' s prepared testimony had been printed online .","depth":7},{"id":270,"text":"It is a bad tweet .","depth":8},{"id":271,"text":"Trying to find something of substance in Comey ' s opening statement like pic.","depth":8},{"id":272,"text":"twitter.com/igLC4JPREg","depth":7},{"id":273,"text":"- GOP","depth":8},{"id":274,"text":"( @ GOP )","depth":8},{"id":275,"text":"June 7 , 2017","depth":7},{"id":276,"text":"It ' s not just a bad tweet","depth":6},{"id":277,"text":"because it ' s such an unforced error","depth":8},{"id":278,"text":"( why did they feel the need","depth":9},{"id":279,"text":"to tweet anything at all ? ) ,","depth":9},{"id":280,"text":"or because the only reason","depth":9},{"id":281,"text":"that Comey ' s opening statement didn ' t feel revelatory","depth":9},{"id":282,"text":"is because much of it had been reported previously in scoops","depth":9},{"id":283,"text":"that many Republicans had dismissed as \" fake news . \"","depth":9},{"id":284,"text":"It ' s a bad tweet","depth":6},{"id":285,"text":"because the combination of the GIF ' s Western setting","depth":11},{"id":286,"text":"( it ' s from the recent remake of The Magnificent Seven )","depth":11},{"id":287,"text":"and the text evoke the HBO show Westworld -","depth":10},{"id":288,"text":"where robots ,","depth":11},{"id":289,"text":"programmed","depth":12},{"id":290,"text":"to believe","depth":13},{"id":291,"text":"they live in the Wild West ,","depth":13},{"id":292,"text":"respond to any sign of the modern world with a blank stare and a \" It doesn ' t look like anything to me . \"","depth":10},{"id":293,"text":"\" It doesn ' t look like anything to me \" is the GOP ' s pre-programmed response to any new sign of wrongdoing by President Trump or his administration .","depth":10},{"id":294,"text":"And some of them have been using it so readily for so long","depth":11},{"id":295,"text":"that it seems they ' ve lost any ability","depth":12},{"id":296,"text":"to actually see the information","depth":14},{"id":297,"text":"amassed in front of them","depth":14},{"id":298,"text":"- much less to draw a line","depth":14},{"id":299,"text":"at which ,","depth":15},{"id":300,"text":"should Trump cross it ,","depth":16},{"id":301,"text":"they ' d be forced to stand up to him .","depth":16},{"id":302,"text":"This is forcing them into uncomfortable positions","depth":11},{"id":303,"text":"-","depth":12},{"id":304,"text":"Speaker of the House Paul Ryan found himself excusing the president as \" new to this \" as a way","depth":13},{"id":305,"text":"of saying","depth":14},{"id":306,"text":"he hadn ' t knowingly screwed up ,","depth":15},{"id":307,"text":"which is just not something you want to say about your commander-in-chief .","depth":15},{"id":308,"text":"But it also means that they have blinded themselves with loyalty to a man","depth":11},{"id":309,"text":"who isn ' t loyal to them .","depth":11},{"id":310,"text":"Donald Trump puts himself before his party .","depth":9},{"id":311,"text":"He puts himself before his own administration -","depth":10},{"id":312,"text":"he was willing to see \" satellites \" brought up on charges in the Russia investigation","depth":11},{"id":313,"text":"as long as he was publicly known not to have been within its scope .","depth":11},{"id":314,"text":"If there is a way","depth":11},{"id":315,"text":"that Trump can get out of this","depth":12},{"id":316,"text":"by undermining Republicans ,","depth":12},{"id":317,"text":"he will do it .","depth":10},{"id":318,"text":"But now ,","depth":10},{"id":319,"text":"while they are the ones with the power","depth":12},{"id":320,"text":"to undermine him ,","depth":12},{"id":321,"text":"they won ' t .","depth":11}],"relations":[{"parent":643,"left":473,"right":642,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":473,"left":344,"right":472,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":344,"left":325,"right":343,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":325,"left":324,"right":3,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":324,"left":323,"right":2,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"